From 6bbb2b5d279eba1bd80edfa3d347fbe6db847eda Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2026 00:46:54 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] soc: hpe: add GXP CHIF driver

Add support for the HPE GXP Channel Interface (CHIF) which provides
bidirectional communication between the BMC and host CPU. The driver
exposes a character device (/dev/chif24) for userspace applications
to exchange packets with the host via DMA-coherent shared memory.

Features:
- 1MB DMA-coherent shared memory with 32-channel CCB table
- Doorbell interrupt handling for packet notifications
- Read/write interface for packet exchange
- Sysfs interface for protocol header inspection

Co-developed-by: Gilbert Chen <gilbert.chen@hpe.com>
Signed-off-by: Gilbert Chen <gilbert.chen@hpe.com>
Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
---
 drivers/soc/hpe/Kconfig    |  12 +
 drivers/soc/hpe/Makefile   |   1 +
 drivers/soc/hpe/gxp-chif.c | 719 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 732 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/soc/hpe/gxp-chif.c

